As of the [[2010 United States census]], there were 386 people in 156 households in the town. The racial makeup of the town was 93 percent [[White (U.S. Census)|white]] and 4 percent [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]].

The population was 67 percent male and 33 percent female. The population was 4.7 percent under the age of 18, and 2.6 percent was 65 or older.

